,'Sword for an Officer of the Town Guards, Northern Italy, circa 1550','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'',14),(343,0,'','THE SNARTEMO SWORD – THE SWORD OF ODIN\nIn the Oslo Museum of Cultural History there is a sword of beauty and power and a connection to our faith and a World War Two adventure.  Unearthed from the grave of a powerful chieftain around 550 CE, the Snartemo Sword is one of Norway’s most extraordinary treasures. The chieftain was laid to rest on a bearskin, dressed in fine garments, surrounded by weapons, tools, a gold ring, and a rare Roman glass cup with a greenish hue and silver rim.\nThe sword’s hilt is unique—a wooden core covered in gilded silver and gold plates, crafted by master smiths in southeastern Norway. The plates depict mythical figures tied to Odin (Wōdinaz in Proto Norse) and the elite warrior ideology of the age. The ring on the hilt may have symbolized a binding oath between the chieftain and his followers—an oath upon an oath. Its worn parts show it was treasured and used long before burial. We in the Tribe swear our oaths on the hilt of the blade – most of us on the Tribe sword.  The iron blade still bears traces of its wooden scabbard, once covered in thin leather.\nA gilded belt buckle from the scabbard’s bandolier—decorated with gold filigree and red garnet—is of a rare type in Norway, but similar to finds from Scania, Sweden.\nDuring World War II, the Snartemo Sword became the focus of a real-life Indiana Jones episode. The German occupation authorities sought it for its potential archaeological importance, and—given SS Reichsfuehrer Heinrich Himmler’s esoteric interests—for its perceived power. In 1939, Norway’s Historical Museum hid its most valuable artifacts in a bank vault in Valdres, 200 km from Oslo. After the 1940 invasion of Norway, the Germans tried to acquire the sword, possibly as a gift for Himmler, and again in 1941 for propaganda display, then in 1942 to make a replica—all requests refused. This story is almost like some of those of the Indiana Jones series of films – yet this one is true.  The sword of Odin is a powerful object.  At the time the word was made our Chief Gods\' name in Proto Norse was Wodinaz and further in the Germanic areas Wotan or Woutan and in Anglo Saxon areas Woden.\nA copy was eventually produced from photographs and given to Vidkun Quisling, Norway’s Nazi-aligned leader, for his residence Gimli—named for the hall of the righteous survivors after Ragnarök. After the war, in 1946, the original sword was returned safely to the museum, and the replica recovered from Quisling’s home (now Norway’s Holocaust Center).\nThe Snartemo Sword is a unique and incredible object—born of the Migration Period but deeply bound to our heathen faith. Its gold plates still gleam with intertwined beasts, Odin’s presence, and the oaths of a chieftain who led in life and was honored in death.\nImages by the Chieftain of the original sword in the Historik Museum in Oslo, the replica made for Quisling and the original fragment of the embroidered sword belt. \n#snartemosword #swordofodin','','','','Snartemo sword','','','','','','','','','','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2',NULL,NULL,NULL,'1','https://www.facebook.com/odinswarriortribe/posts/pfbid02bhBuu5NwjFGX9Wtf1T8xJV5xNSxSdN3sXTZDjBM1v9k6yVQ2ATG8qZE8iGYsCZyil','','',14),(344,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Skofnung','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'',14),(345,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Sigismond little present to York, 1416, Mansion House, York','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'',14),(346,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Sainte Anastasie Sword','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'',14),(347,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Rapier of Prince-Elector Christian II of Saxony Israel Schuech  (German, Dres